      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; model form adequacy is addressed through output comparison.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model with the Giersiepen hemolysis power-law was selected based on published literature for centrifugal pump hemolysis. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be traceable to measurement data or published material properties with documented sources.",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties (viscosity, density), boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure), and pump geometry were sourced from FDA benchmark documentation and manufacturer drawings. A comprehensive Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed sampling all 14 model inputs simultaneously to propagate input variability through to the RH output distribution, yielding a 95th-percentile RH of 0.87 against the RH < 1 criterion."
    },
